{"id":43897,"date":"2025-07-04T17:58:55","date_gmt":"2025-07-04T13:58:55","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=43897"},"modified":"2025-07-04T17:59:25","modified_gmt":"2025-07-04T13:59:25","slug":"ahmad-dua-forgiveness-better","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/07\/04\/ahmad-dua-forgiveness-better\/","title":{"rendered":"Ahmad on Dua: Prayer against oppressors allowed, but forgiveness better"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Ibn Muflih reported: Imam Ahmad ibn Hanbal, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cSupplication is a proportional punishment. Whoever supplicates against the one who wronged him, he has not been patient.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Imam Ibn Muflih commented, \u201cBy that he means the supplicant has retaliated. Retaliation is permissible, but the Almighty said: <strong>Whoever endures patiently and forgives, surely this is a resolve to aspire to<\/strong>, (42:23)\u2026 If one supplicates against the wrongdoer to be hurt by the same amount with which he was hurt by him, that is justice.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Furu\u0304&#8217; wa Tas\u0323h\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Furu\u0304&#8217; 10\/123<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0645\u0641\u0644\u062d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0625\u0650\u0645\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064f \u0623\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0645\u064e\u062f\u064f \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0627\u0644\u062f\u064f\u0651\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0621\u064f \u0642\u0650\u0635\u064e\u0627\u0635\u064c \u0648\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062f\u064e\u0639\u064e\u0627 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0638\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0645\u0650\u0647\u0650 \u0641\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0635\u064e\u0628\u064e\u0631\u064e<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0645\u0641\u0644\u062d \u0